      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities should be evaluated for their relevance to the specific COU, including geometry, loading, and material representativeness.",
      "rationale": "This factor was considered by the assessment team but judged inapplicable to the present COU because the validation experiment is the COU itself — the ASTM F1717 bench test is both the reference standard and the context of intended use. The team concluded that a separate relevance evaluation would be circular and therefore did not conduct a structured assessment. No gradation level was assigned. Note: the correct encoding for this determination would be factorStatus 'not-applicable'; the 'not-assessed' status used here reflects that no formal relevance scoring was performed and the rationale was not subjected to independent review."
