  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors were formally assessed. Eleven factors met or exceeded their required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this gap was acknowledged and judged acceptable given that the ASTM F1717 protocol is a standardized, regulatory-recognized test method and the single-condition limitation is disclosed in the submission. The thirteenth factor (Relevance of the validation activities to the COU) was not formally assessed on the basis that the validation experiment is co-extensive with the COU; this determination was not independently reviewed. Overall credibility evidence was judged sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim at assurance level Medium. Decision: Accepted.",
